output_list.impact: Integer overflow in mintToken function allows the owner to set the balance of an arbitrary user to any value.
The freezeAccount function allows the owner to set the freeze status of an arbitrary user, which can be used to create role-based access controls.
The setPrices function is publicly available, allowing any user to set the prices used by the contract. This can be used to create role-based access controls.
Integer overflow in buy function allows the owner to set the balance of the contract to any value.
Integer overflow in sell function allows the owner to set the balance of the contract to any value.
